</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Goshan's Topic of the day - Using slow</span><hr size=1> The primary use of slow is to mitigate damage done upon your groups by mobs. Drop a Shiftless <br>
deeds or a Forlorn deeds on a mob and they become pussycats. <br>
<br>
You can however use slow to help balance your mana vs the clerics mana to make your groups more effecient. If you find yourself low on mana a lot in a particular group because you are having to buff/crowd control/slow/charm/etc.. you can simply not cast slow on the next couple of mobs. This will make the cleric work a bit harder and use a bit more mana to heal the tanks but it will allow you to regain mana while they expend. You dont want to make them go oom while you are full mana of course. Just pay attn to what the cleric says when a mana check is called. If they are at 80+ and you are at 40ish or below, dont slow the next couple mobs. This will keep your mana and the clerics mana balanced so your group can operate at peak effeciency.<br>
<br>
Slow is also an effective form of crowd control against mobs that cannot be mezed. A slowed Giant or Juggernaut doesnt do a lot of damage at all. With cleric buffs and bedlam/beserker spirit, you can tank most anything if it is slowed. So in those 3 jugg pulls try Gok/Rapture on one and just slow the other one. It will beat on you but you can easily get spells off inbwetween volleys enabling you to slow the current target and keep they other mezed. It will make your crowd control a lot less hectic and easier to manage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usaeliashadowfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saelia Shadowfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(3/21/01 1:24:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Goshan's Topic of the day - Using slow</span><hr size=1> You forgot to address Shammys.  The Shaman slow is always a step ahead of ours.  If you have a Shaman in the group that is capable of expending the mana, you should have them doing this instead.<br>
<br>
Now, in my regular group, the shammy's the primary healer.  Right now we have her slowing, but I'm considering re-claiming that duty since she's more frequently oom than I am.  Problem is, many of my regular groupmates would rather have me at full mana, sitting on my ass in case something goes wrong.  I don't know about the rest of you, but I find it hard to sit on my thumbs while my friends are taking a beating.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
