<i>Public Relations Rep</i><br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(3/21/01 11:04:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Goshan's Topic of the day - Using slow</span><hr size=1> There is a chart, where , for a little while in an enchanters life, our slow is actually BETTER than shaman slow.  This occurs somtetime in the mid 20s, till shaman get tagars insects at level 29.  Once they get that spell, shaman slow is AWLAYS better than ours.  It makes mobs slower, casts faster, and uses less mana.<br>
<br>
Add that to the fact that at 50+, your typical shaman has 800+ AC at a minimum, and at around 55 ish with standard gear for that level MANY are pushing 900+, and you see that shaman are MUCH better equipped to slow than we are.<br>
<br>
With that being said, at 57 our slow is almost as slow as theirs ( 70 percent for ours, and 75 percent for theirs ), so we can do a damn fine job of slowing if there is no shaman.<br>
<br>
Also, i slow as Goshan said, to help manage mana output for myself and the cleric.<br>
<br>
